article.headline: Loyola, Md. 73, Howard 58
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP)-Gerald Brown scored 33 points to lead Loyola to a 73-58 win over Howard in the Philly Classic on Friday. Brown shot 9-of-19 from the field and 13-of-14 at the line for Loyola (4-2) and led all scorers. Eugene Myatt had 17 points and seven rebounds for Howard (2-3). Loyola led 36-25 at the break. In the second half, Loyola put the game away by converting 12 of 13 chances at the free-throw line to extend the lead. Howard was just 2-of-13 from behind the 3-point arc and committed 18 turnovers in the loss.
